 Dcode Instruction Set (v2)
 🔹 Variables
- `var:name=value` → Declare and assign variable  
  Example: `var:x=10`

🔹 Printing & Math
- `print:text` → Print text or variable values
- `print:expression` → Evaluate math (+, -, *, /, ^)
- `print:root:value,n` → Calculate n‑th root of value
- `print:exp:base,exponent` → Calculate base^exponent
- `print:random:min,max` → Generate random integer between min and max

 🔹 Arduino (stubs)
- `arduino:compile` → Compile Arduino sketch
- `arduino:upload` → Upload Arduino sketch
- `arduino:serial:...` → Send serial command

🔹 Input
- `input:keyboard:KEY` → Check if key is pressed (A, B, C, SPACE, ENTER, ESC)
- `input:mouse` → Get mouse position

🔹 Networking
- `net:bluetooth:scan` → Scan Bluetooth devices
- `net:wifi:list` → List Wi‑Fi networks
 
🔹 Utilities
- `console:clear` → Clear console output
- `console:log:msg` → Log message to console

 🔹 AI Lifecycle
- `ai:create:model [params]`
  Example: `ai:create:model name=ModelA layers=3 units=128 optimizer=adam loss=mse metrics=accuracy`
- `ai:train [params]`
  Example: `ai:train model=ModelA dataset=train.csv epochs=10 batch=32 device=GPU`
- `ai:evaluate [params]`
  Example: `ai:evaluate model=ModelA dataset=validation.csv metrics=accuracy,precision`
- `ai:visualize type=<loss|accuracy>` → Shows training curves
- `ai:run input=<file>` → Runs inference
- `ai:test input=<file> expected=<file>` → Compares predictions vs expected
- `ai:status` → Prints current models and device
- `ai:reset` → Clears all models and resets device to CPU

🔹 Persistence
- `ai:save path=<file>` → Save model state
- `ai:load path=<file>` → Load model state
- `ai:export format=<onnx|json> path=<file>` → Export model
- `ai:import path=<file>` → Import model
- `ai:share path=<file> target=<repo>` → Share model externally

 🔹 Device Control
- `ai:set:device <CPU|GPU|NPU>` → Switch execution device
 🔹 Dataset Handling
- `ai:load:dataset path=<file>` → Load dataset (simulated row count)


